-03-11 18:43 EDT] blance of usage limit in claude\\nassistant: The Claude CLI doesn't expose usage/billing info directly. There are two separate things here:\\n\\n### 1. **Claude Code CLI** (what we just used)\\n- Uses your **Claude Pro subscription** (OAuth login)\\n- No built-in command to check remaining usage\\n- You can check at: **[claude.ai/settings](https://claude.ai/settings)** or the account dashboard\\n\\n### 2. **OpenClaw** (this agent, me)\\n- Also uses your Claude subscription via OAuth\\nassistant: Unfortunately there's no direct CLI command to check your Claude Pro usage balance. Best way to check:\\n\\n👉 **Go to [claude.ai/settings](https://claude.ai/settings)** in your browser — it'll show your usage across the 5-hour and 7-day windows.\\n\\nFrom your last check (March 8), you were at 11% of 5hr and 3% of 7-day, so you've been well within limits. That one Hello World task would've barely made a dent.\\nuser: System: [2026-03-11 18:43:56 EDT] Exec failed (brisk-sh, signal SIGTERM) :: ctive · default claude-opus-4-6 (200k ctx) · ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json │ └─────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────…\",\n  \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-11-claude-login.md\"\n}"}],"details":{"text":"user: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-11 18:21 EDT] I did login\nassistant: Claude Code built it! Here's what was created:\n\n- **`index.js`** — `console.log(\"Hello, World!\")`\n- **`package.json`** — with `npm start` script\n- **`README.md`** — updated with description and run instructions\n\nLet's verify it works:\nassistant: ✅ **Hello, World!** — running perfectly. Want to build on it or try something more complex?\nuser: System: [2026-03-11 18:21:59 EDT] Exec completed (plaid-du, code 0) :: Done. Three files created/updated: - `package.json` — with `npm start` script - `index.js` — prints \"Hello, World!\